st ratio<br />\nassumption: working class individual<br />\ncase 1: unemployed/underemployed with low pay =&gt; low cost, low benefit =&gt; low benefit to cost ratio<br />\ncase 2: gainfully employed with reasonable pay =&gt; low to medium cost, medium benefit =&gt; medium benefit to cost ratio<br />\ncase 3: very gainfully employed with diminishing marginal returns beyond reasonable pay =&gt; high cost, medium to high benefit =&gt; lower benefit to cost ratio<br />\ncase 2 optimal"},{"pid":"e588d17f8786e3de48f8fddb4a258e459f662047","tid":581875,"uid":84691,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-03-06T02:15:00.000Z","msg":"咁點解你唔做自己鍾意既野<br />\n<br />\n興趣同事業唔可以共存<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/wonder.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"}]}